    <div class="section">
      <a name="1.3"></a>
      <h2>PARTITIPANT INSTITUTIONS</h2>
      <p>One of the objectives of theMESMIS project was the consolidation of a multi-institutional and interdisciplinaryresearch team, where institutions and organizations involved in natural resources management come together. This group now consists of four academic institutions and one civil organization: The Ecosystems Research Center(CIECO-UNAM), Environmental Geography Research Center(CIGA-UNAM), Research Center in Agriculture Sciences (CICA-UAEM), College of the Southern Borderland (ECOSUR) and the Interdisciplinary Group of Appropriate Rural Technology (GIRA, A.C.) </p>
      <p>This group collaborates in graduate courses in different universities, training workshops, in the generation of reference material and documents as well as in national and international publications. Also, all members adviseundergraduate and graduate theses and dissertations as well as local, national and international studies. </p>
      <p>Simultaneously, each member keeps close ties with institutions in Latin America, Spain, Holland and France, mainly in the education field. This contributes tocreating a space for exchangingacademic as well as sustainability evaluation experiences. </p>
      <p>The formation of this research team has helped to strengthen the theoretical bases of sustainability evaluation and its application in concrete experiences. Today, it is in a stage of consolidation and its objective is to improve the conceptual and practicaltools to be usedby different agents involved in natural resources management.  </p>
